what you need the most.

05:23.859 --> 05:25.026
I need a leaf spring.

05:25.927 --> 05:26.895
Griffin.

05:26.928 --> 05:29.197
(SOFT MUSIC)

06:37.773 --> 06:42.645
(DOG BARKING)
(SOFT MUSIC)

07:18.018 --> 07:19.653
You wanna be real careful.

07:19.686 --> 07:21.855
You just wanna cut the skin.

07:21.888 --> 07:23.323
You don't wanna
slice the organs.

07:23.357 --> 07:25.559
You don't wanna
puncture the stomach

07:25.659 --> 07:28.229
'cause it'll make a mess
and it'll spoil the meat.

07:29.330 --> 07:34.335
(SOFT MUSIC)
(KNIVES CLANKING)

07:50.553 --> 07:53.189
Every animal in the
forest has enough brains

07:53.223 --> 07:55.192
to tan its own hide.

07:57.194 --> 07:58.162
Except one.

07:58.195 --> 07:59.830
A moose.

07:59.864 --> 08:02.099
(SOFT MUSIC)

08:12.778 --> 08:14.213
ANNE: 200 is an insult.

08:15.214 --> 08:16.249
I had to cut our supplies.

08:16.282 --> 08:18.284
I couldn't get any food.

08:18.384 --> 08:21.287
I'll have to go back next
week with castor sides.

08:21.387 --> 08:23.524
It's the season.

08:23.557 --> 08:25.759
People don't need
fur 'til it's cold.

08:25.793 --> 08:28.062
Prices are a quarter of
what they were two years ago.

08:28.095 --> 08:29.396
Costs are almost double.

08:30.464 --> 08:33.201
Muskrats are worthless
so I'll stop baiting them.

08:33.234 --> 08:36.236
Put down more body grips from
Martin's down at the river.

08:37.472 --> 08:39.541
Castors out there steady.

08:39.573 --> 08:40.642
Beavers are worth it.

08:42.409 --> 08:44.413
ANNE: Take it off the table.

08:44.580 --> 08:45.548
I'm working on it.

08:45.581 --> 08:47.249
Not while we eat.

08:54.424 --> 08:56.326
My love, how was your day?

08:57.761 --> 08:59.796
Dad let me do everything.

08:59.830 --> 09:02.233
I found this weird bug with
orange hair all over it.

09:02.266 --> 09:03.968
A bug with orange hair?

09:04.001 --> 09:05.303
Yeah, Tova ate it.

09:05.336 --> 09:07.171
What kind was it?

09:07.271 --> 09:08.272
Did you ask your dad?

09:09.507 --> 09:10.942
Never heard a name for it.

09:12.144 --> 09:14.012
Bug with orange
hair is fine though.

09:16.181 --> 09:17.983
And the wolf is back.

09:18.016 --> 09:19.985
Ate a raccoon and left the paw.

09:20.018 --> 09:21.688
The back leg.

09:26.192 --> 09:28.294
You weren't gonna tell me?

09:28.328 --> 09:29.996
I didn't wanna
upset you again.

09:34.635 --> 09:36.103
Renee, take your
food into your room.

09:36.137 --> 09:37.171
Can't I just cover my ears?

09:37.204 --> 09:39.306
Do as you're told please.

09:39.340 --> 09:40.675
Won't be long.

09:41.343 --> 09:42.677
Go on.

09:51.487 --> 09:53.189
You were gonna put us
in danger with no warning?

09:53.222 --> 09:54.323
We're in no danger.

09:56.225 --> 09:58.194
It's just a hungry wolf
looking for an easy meal.

09:58.227 --> 09:59.228
It's the same one.

10:03.200 --> 10:04.668
Something's bringing it back.

10:05.869 --> 10:07.304
Either it's food
or it's a female.

10:07.337 --> 10:08.805
If I find out what
it's attracted to,

10:08.839 --> 10:09.807
I could use it to bait it.

10:09.841 --> 10:11.176
It's attracted to us.

10:12.510 --> 10:13.478
It's taking from the trap line.

10:13.511 --> 10:15.747
It already knows we're
a steady food supply.

10:20.219 --> 10:21.520
We're reporting it this time.

10:26.025 --> 10:27.893
Fish cops gonna do
something I can't?

10:29.262 --> 10:30.397
Maybe they can catch it.

10:34.034 --> 10:35.570
We don't run
from our troubles.

10:36.571 --> 10:37.838
We bring our problems to them.

10:37.872 --> 10:39.340
They bring their problems to us.

10:39.373 --> 10:41.442
At least I have good reason
to be worried about the wolf.

10:41.542 --> 10:42.510
You're scared of people.

10:42.543 --> 10:43.878
Enough.

10:49.718 --> 10:51.753
I'll go out tomorrow morning.

10:51.787 --> 10:54.256
If it's there, I will catch it.

10:54.289 --> 10:56.425
It's not just the wolf.

10:56.458 --> 10:58.962
The garden's done and
we can't afford food.

10:59.062 --> 11:00.430
The season's turned
and we have no money

11:00.463 --> 11:01.764
for the winter move.

11:01.798 --> 11:03.566
What if we can't make it
out before the freeze?

11:06.971 --> 11:08.272
What's the end of this?

11:11.442 --> 11:12.577
Say what you're gonna say.

11:22.954 --> 11:24.422
Just think about it.

11:25.490 --> 11:26.959
We got no money for food.

11:28.928 --> 11:30.597
We're gonna buy a
house in the city.

11:30.631 --> 11:31.897
Kearney isn't a city.

11:31.931 --> 11:33.833
It isn't even a town,
but there's a school

11:33.933 --> 11:36.837
and it's still close
enough to the trap line.

11:36.937 --> 11:37.904
We could talk to a bank.

11:37.938 --> 11:39.607
I could get a job.

11:43.277 --> 11:44.511
She's been in
there long enough.

11:44.612 --> 11:46.114
She's gonna think
we're punishing her.

11:47.448 --> 11:48.416
We'll talk about this later.

11:48.449 --> 11:49.450
Yeah.

11:51.319 --> 11:52.688
(SOFT MUSIC)

11:52.787 --> 11:55.659
He was mastered by the
sheer sure dream of life.

11:55.692 --> 11:57.459
The tidal wave of being.

11:57.493 --> 12:01.330
The perfect joy of each separate
muscle, joint and sinew,

12:01.363 --> 12:04.367
and that it was everything
that was not death.

12:04.467 --> 12:06.536
That it was a glow and rampant.

12:07.537 --> 12:09.005
Mom, what does rampant mean?

12:10.040 --> 12:11.441
I'm not sure.

12:11.474 --> 12:12.442
You're all done.

12:12.475 --> 12:13.612
Go get ready for bed.

12:13.645 --> 12:16.180
(SOFT MUSIC)

12:27.993 --> 12:29.194
This is a hard life.

12:32.030 --> 12:34.467
Life is hard everywhere.

12:34.500 --> 12:36.169
This is harder.

12:37.036 --> 12:38.404
You chose it and it suits you.

12:40.573 --> 12:42.376
I chose it when I chose you.

12:44.713 --> 12:46.380
And it suits me.

12:49.550 --> 12:51.085
Renee never had a choice.

12:55.691 --> 12:56.659
She should be in school.

12:56.692 --> 13:00.696
She should be worried
about math and boys.

13:01.429 --> 13:02.531
Not wolves.

13:03.532 --> 13:04.867
She's not scared of a wolf.

13:05.935 --> 13:07.269
You are.

13:09.438 --> 13:10.539
I never finished school.

13:12.209 --> 13:13.845
Does that make me weak?

13:13.877 --> 13:15.879
It's not about
being weak or strong.

13:17.280 --> 13:19.617
People don't live
like this anymore.

13:22.053 --> 13:24.555
It feels like the world
has left us behind.

13:27.125 --> 13:29.394
There isn't another
generation left.

13:31.731 --> 13:33.065
There is if we make one.

13:37.737 --> 13:38.872
This is our life.

13:40.473 --> 13:42.710
This is our home.

13:42.743 --> 13:46.246
Nothing pushes us out
of our home or our life.

13:47.480 --> 13:48.581
Not even you.

13:55.089 --> 13:57.626
(SOFT MUSIC)

14:05.300 --> 14:06.636
ANNE: Goodnight.

14:06.669 --> 14:09.172
(SOFT MUSIC)

14:51.485 --> 14:54.020
(OMINOUS MUSIC)

15:54.789 --> 15:56.691
Not today.

15:56.724 --> 15:57.725
Stay home and help your
mother with the chores.

15:57.759 --> 15:58.726
I wanna help catch him.

15:58.760 --> 16:00.093
You're too young.

16:00.127 --> 16:01.461
First get used to
the animals that run,

16:01.562 --> 16:02.931
then you can hunt
the ones that chase.

16:02.964 --> 16:04.232
Grandpa took
you hunting wolves

16:04.265 --> 16:05.801
when you were eight
and I'm almost 13.

16:05.901 --> 16:07.468
I was twice as mean.

16:07.569 --> 16:08.536
Took me half the time.

16:08.570 --> 16:09.939
I don't have to be mean.

16:09.972 --> 16:11.472
I'm smart.

16:11.573 --> 16:14.109
(OMINOUS MUSIC)

16:16.746 --> 16:18.280
Okay, you can help
with the bait sets,

16:18.314 --> 16:20.050
but we find any fresh tracks,
you take the same path home.

16:20.082 --> 16:21.083
No questions.

16:23.086 --> 16:24.321
Tova stays here.

16:24.421 --> 16:26.057
Go grab your rifle.

16:26.122 --> 16:28.659
(OMINOUS MUSIC)

16:57.625 --> 16:59.860
ANNE: Jo, are you there?

16:59.960 --> 17:01.696
JOSEPH: I'm here, go.

17:01.796 --> 17:03.430
Renee is with you?

17:03.464 --> 17:04.431
JOSEPH: She's here.

17:04.464 --> 17:05.700
She's just baiting sets.

17:05.800 --> 17:07.836
I'll send her back when
it turns into a hunt.

17:09.303 --> 17:10.672
You sure that's safe?

17:11.807 --> 17:12.842
JOSEPH: We're moving up wind.

17:12.875 --> 17:14.777
She follows the same path
back, she'll be fine.

17:14.810 --> 17:15.845
She's got the 22.

17:18.313 --> 17:20.315
Don't make that face.

17:20.348 --> 17:21.483
I know what I'm doing.

17:22.550 --> 17:23.686
We should stay off the walkie.

17:23.720 --> 17:26.957
Buddy trip is so loud, it'll
hear us from a mile away.

17:26.990 --> 17:29.960
(OMINOUS MUSIC)

17:29.993 --> 17:31.194
ANNE: Over and out.

17:31.228 --> 17:33.831
(OMINOUS MUSIC)

17:37.068 --> 17:38.335
Think it's wolf shit.

17:39.671 --> 17:40.639
Come here.

17:40.673 --> 17:43.241
(OMINOUS MUSIC)

17:45.711 --> 17:48.047
I want you to rub this
all over your body.

17:48.080 --> 17:49.180
Get it in deep.

17:50.182 --> 17:51.851
Look at me.

17:52.919 --> 17:55.587
You wanna snag a wolf,
you gotta out wolf them.

17:57.857 --> 18:00.761
That careful son of a bitch is
always looking for traps so.

18:04.865 --> 18:06.167
We gotta be careful, too.

18:07.534 --> 18:09.037
That's for your breath.

18:09.071 --> 18:12.107
(OMINOUS MUSIC)

18:12.206 --> 18:13.574
Yeah.

18:13.607 --> 18:15.043
Come on, let's go.

18:18.380 --> 18:23.019
Without its pack, a lone wolf
won't go for its usual prey.

18:23.052 --> 18:28.058
It'll go for the old, the
young, the sick, dead.

18:29.258 --> 18:30.293
Gotta give him some
of what he wants.

18:32.796 --> 18:36.066
When you're backing up, don't
lean heavy on your footsteps.

18:37.234 --> 18:39.369
Watch how you don't break.

18:39.403 --> 18:42.239
(OMINOUS MUSIC)

18:42.272 --> 18:43.407
What is it?

18:43.440 --> 18:46.077
(OMINOUS MUSIC)

18:52.283 --> 18:53.251
Is it him?

18:53.284 --> 18:56.455
(OMINOUS MUSIC)

18:56.489 --> 18:58.158
Go on home.

18:59.760 --> 19:00.727
Keep your rifle close.

19:00.761 --> 19:02.428
Stay to the path.

19:03.930 --> 19:06.834
If you see anything, you
hear anything, don't run.

19:07.668 --> 19:09.269
Pop a shot off.

19:09.302 --> 19:11.806
Whatever it is,
it'll keep on going.

19:11.839 --> 19:13.607
What do you do if
you see something?

19:13.641 --> 19:14.842
(GUN COCKING)

19:14.942 --> 19:15.911
Don't run.

19:15.944 --> 19:17.980
All right, yeah.

19:19.948 --> 19:22.416
Tell mom I'll be home
after dark, okay?

19:22.450 --> 19:23.786
Go on.

19:24.119 --> 19:26.956
(OMINOUS MUSIC)

20:36.365 --> 20:41.370
(MAN HOWLING)
(OMINOUS MUSIC)

20:42.106 --> 20:44.574
